# Utility Functions

## Core Approach

- Pure functions in `src/utils/` directory
- Single responsibility principle
- Proper TypeScript types with JSDoc documentation
- Export individual functions rather than default exports for better tree-shaking

## Reference Implementations

- **String Processing**: `src/utils/orcidUtils.ts`
  - Input sanitization patterns
  - URL extraction with regex
  - Format validation
  
- **Data Parsing**: `src/utils/parseBBox.tsx`
  - Regex-based string parsing
  - Type-safe return values
  - Null handling for invalid input

- **Data Transformation**: `src/utils/base64ToArrayBuffer.ts`
  - Format conversion utilities
  - Simple, focused functions

## File Organization

- One utility file per domain (e.g., `orcidUtils.ts`, `geoUtils.ts`)
- Export individual functions, not default exports
- Include JSDoc comments for complex functions
